{"TopicId":157624,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"How to have the Navball follow the Kerbal on EVA","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T04:02:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T04:02:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen controlling a vessel, the navball\u00A0doesn\u2019t follow the camera. It follows the vessel. But when controlling a Kerbal, the navball\u00A0follows the camera, not the Kerbal\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny suggestions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T09:35:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157624\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489291325\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny suggestions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake a bug report\u00A0in the coming 1.3 open testing.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA LateUpdate should run after the stock code so you \u0022only\u0022 have to you find out the proper rot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003ELateUpdate()\n{\n\tNabBall nav = FindObjectOfType\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;KSP.UI.Screens.Flight.NavBall\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E() // cache somewhere\n\tnav.navBall.roation = ???\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T12:03:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157624\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489311351\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake a bug report\u00A0in the coming 1.3 open testing.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA LateUpdate should run after the stock code so you \u0022only\u0022 have to you find out the proper rot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan\u003ELateUpdate\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E()\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ENabBall\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E nav \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EFindObjectOfType\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EKSP\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EUI\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EScreens\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cs